      "description": "Presenting a concours-level 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This example maintains its factory-spec boost pattern and vacuum line integrity, ensuring linear power delivery across the rev range. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, supported by its original double-wishbone suspension architecture and a 50:50 weight distribution. Power is managed via a precise 5-speed manual gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Every panel reflects its factory finish, and the interior demonstrates zero UV degradation or bolster wear. A true turn-key investment for the discerning enthusiast.",
